# 🔐 Stripe Keys — Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your real Stripe keys.

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

## Variables

| Variable | Description | Where to Find It |
|---|---|---|
| `VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` | Your Stripe publishable key (starts with `pk_live_` or `pk_test_`) | Stripe Dashboard → Developers → API keys |
| `VITE_API_URL` | Backend API base URL (dev: `http://localhost:3001`, prod: your server URL) | Your deployed backend address |
| `VITE_STRIPE_PRICE_SERUM` | Price ID for Bakuchiol Serum one-time purchase | Stripe Dashboard → Products → [Product] → Pricing |
| `VITE_STRIPE_PRICE_REFILL` | Price ID for Bakuchiol Serum Refill | Same as above |
| `VITE_STRIPE_PRICE_SHOWER` | Price ID for Filtered Showerhead one-time | Same as above |
| `VITE_STRIPE_PRICE_FILTER` | Price ID for Shower Filter Replacement | Same as above |
| `VITE_STRIPE_PRICE_LAMP` | Price ID for Japandi Table Lamp | Same as above |
| `VITE_STRIPE_PRICE_SERUM_SUB` | Price ID for Serum Subscription (recurring) | Stripe Dashboard → Products → Create recurring price |
| `VITE_STRIPE_PRICE_FILTER_SUB` | Price ID for Filter Subscription (recurring) | Same as above |

## Backend Server Variables (see `server/.env.example`)

| Variable | Description |
|---|---|
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | Server-side secret key (starts with `sk_live_` or `sk_test_`) |
| `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET` | Webhook signing secret (starts with `whsec_`) |
| `PORT` | Server port (default: 3001) |
| `CLIENT_ORIGIN` | Frontend URL for CORS (default: `http://localhost:5173`) |

## How to Set Up Stripe Products

1. **Create a Stripe account**: https://dashboard.stripe.com/register
2. **Create Products**: Go to Stripe Dashboard → Products → Add Product
3. **Add prices**: For one-time purchases, add a "One-time" price. For subscriptions, add a "Recurring" price (monthly/quarterly).
4. **Copy Price IDs**: Each price will have an ID like `price_1AbCdEfGhIjKlMnO`. Copy these into your `.env` file.

## Testing

For testing with Stripe test mode:
- Use `pk_test_...` publishable key (frontend)
- Use `sk_test_...` secret key (backend)
- Test card: `4242 4242 4242 4242` (any future date, any CVC)

For live mode:
- Use `pk_live_...` publishable key
- Use `sk_live_...` secret key (backend only — never expose client-side)

## Security Warning

⚠️ **Never commit your `.env` file to version control** — it contains secret API keys.
The `.env.example` file in this repo has placeholders only.